To convert Markdown-formatted text to HTML-formatted text in C++, you can use the `boost::algorithm::replace_all_copy` function from the Boost C++ libraries along with the corresponding Markdown and HTML character escaping functions from the Markdown library (e.g., using the `libdoxygen` implementation).

Here's an example implementation of a `markdownToHtml` function that converts a given Markdown-formatted `std::string` into an equivalent HTML-formatted string using Boost and Markdown libraries:

